1
00:00:01,420 --> 00:00:06,650
Chaikin Money Flow is a technical indicator
which determines if an instrument is under

2
00:00:06,650 --> 00:00:08,900
accumulation or distribution.

3
00:00:08,900 --> 00:00:13,590
The Chaikin Money Flow compares the closing
price to the high-low range of the trading

4
00:00:13,590 --> 00:00:14,830
session.

5
00:00:14,830 --> 00:00:19,400
• if the price closes near the high of the
session with increased volume, the Chaikin

6
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:23,880
Money Flow increases in value
• if the price closes near the low of the

7
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:29,710
session with increased volume, the Chaikin
Money Flow decreases in value.

8
00:00:29,710 --> 00:00:35,170
Chaikin Money Flow measures buying and selling
pressure over a set period of time and is

9
00:00:35,170 --> 00:00:39,969
a popular indicator among the traders who
use volume technical analysis.

10
00:00:39,969 --> 00:00:46,170
Along with the On Balance Volume, the Chaikin
Money Flow is tracking the Money Flow on a

11
00:00:46,170 --> 00:00:47,170
market.

12
00:00:47,170 --> 00:00:50,660
What are the setting of this volume indicator?

13
00:00:50,660 --> 00:00:57,530
Traders generally use 20-periods or 21-periods
for calculating the Chaikin Money Flow indicator.

14
00:00:57,530 --> 00:01:03,670
Some traders also use the 50-period Chaikin
Money Flow to determine the accumulation /distribution

15
00:01:03,670 --> 00:01:06,150
on the longer term.

16
00:01:06,150 --> 00:01:12,079
• Chaikin Money Flow settings with values
over 30 make the indicator less sensitive.

17
00:01:12,079 --> 00:01:15,049
This will result in fewer, but better quality
signals

18
00:01:15,049 --> 00:01:22,380
• Chaikin Money Flow settings with values
below 20 make the indicator over-sensitive.

19
00:01:22,380 --> 00:01:25,460
This will result in more market noise.

20
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:30,390
Lower settings on the Chaikin Money Flow indicator
should be carefully traded, as it can lead

21
00:01:30,390 --> 00:01:33,840
to many false signals

22
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:40,109
How To Read Chaikin Money Flow
Chaikin Money Flow is used by traders to confirm

23
00:01:40,109 --> 00:01:41,609
the market trend.

24
00:01:41,609 --> 00:01:51,100
CMF values above zero indicate an uptrend
while CMF values below zero suggest a downtrend.

25
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:55,340
• when the Chaikin Money Flow indicator
is above 0-level this is a bullish signal

26
00:01:55,340 --> 00:02:01,159
• when the Chaikin Money Flow indicator
is below 0-level this is a bearish signal

27
00:02:01,159 --> 00:02:10,560
The Chaikin Money Flow usually stays between
-0.5 and 0.5 levels and rarely reaches its

28
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:15,909
maximum/minimum values of -1 and 1.

29
00:02:15,909 --> 00:02:21,360
A movement of the Chaikin Money Flow oscillator
from negative to positive or vice versa does

30
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:23,680
not suggest a change in trend.

31
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:30,310
So remember this observation because in choppy
markets the CMF generates many false signals.

32
00:02:30,310 --> 00:02:36,980
The Chaikin Money Flow is also used by traders
to confirm the strength behind an uptrend

33
00:02:36,980 --> 00:02:37,980
or a downtrend.

34
00:02:37,980 --> 00:02:44,450
In this regard, the indicator resembles the
Average Directional Movement (ADX), which

35
00:02:44,450 --> 00:02:48,659
also measures trend strength.

36
00:02:48,659 --> 00:02:54,159
Chaikin Money Flow confirms the breakouts
of support and resistance levels.

37
00:02:54,159 --> 00:03:00,430
During an uptrend, if a breakout of a resistance
occurs while the CMF reaches new highs, this

38
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:04,350
suggests that the bulls are taking control
of the market.

39
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:10,439
This is a signal of an uptrend continuation
During a downtrend, if a breakout of a support

40
00:03:10,439 --> 00:03:16,239
occurs while the CMF reaches new lows, this
suggests that the bears are taking control

41
00:03:16,239 --> 00:03:18,019
of the market.

42
00:03:18,019 --> 00:03:24,890
This is a signal of a downtrend continuation
However, the Chaikin Money Flow has a flaw.

43
00:03:24,890 --> 00:03:28,540
The CMF is not handling gaps very well.

44
00:03:28,540 --> 00:03:35,090
For example, if a gap occurs on the upside
and closes at a lower price, the money flow

45
00:03:35,090 --> 00:03:41,329
would give you a negative figure, despite
the bullish price increase.

46
00:03:41,329 --> 00:03:44,439
How to Read Market Conditions with Chaikin
Money Flow

47
00:03:44,439 --> 00:03:53,420
• values between 0.05 – 0.25 indicate
buying pressures from the bulls.

48
00:03:53,420 --> 00:03:59,980
This is a sign of accumulation and that the
market trades in an uptrend.

49
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:07,650
• values between 0.25 – 0.4 indicate that
the bulls are in control of the market.

50
00:04:07,650 --> 00:04:10,930
This indicates that the market is in a strong
uptrend

51
00:04:10,930 --> 00:04:19,630
• values between 0.4 – 1 indicate that
the bulls are in full control of the market.

52
00:04:19,630 --> 00:04:22,830
This indicates that the market is in a very
strong uptrend

53
00:04:22,830 --> 00:04:34,200
• values between -0.05 – -0.25 indicate
selling pressures from the bears.

54
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:39,390
This is a sign of distribution and that the
market trades in a downtrend.

55
00:04:39,390 --> 00:04:48,260
• values between -0.25 – -0.4 indicate
that the bears are in control of the market.

56
00:04:48,260 --> 00:04:50,660
This indicates that the market is in a strong
downtrend

57
00:04:50,660 --> 00:05:00,120
• values between -0.4 – -1 indicate that
the bears are in full control of the market.

58
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:02,960
This indicates that the market is in a very
strong downtrend

59
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:12,870
• values between -0.05 – 0.05 signals
a decision-making period.

60
00:05:12,870 --> 00:05:18,000
When the CMF trades between these levels,
the bulls and bears are putting pressure to

61
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,500
take control of the market.

62
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:26,320
This area is often marked by choppiness and
is better to be avoided.

63
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:33,280
How To Trade With Chaikin Money Flow
One of the most common ways in which traders

64
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:38,150
use the Chaikin Money Flow indicator is to
take signals when the oscillator crosses the

65
00:05:38,150 --> 00:05:40,090
zero level.

66
00:05:40,090 --> 00:05:44,300
• when CMF indicator crosses above zero,
a buy signal is generated

67
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:50,970
• when CMF indicator crosses below zero,
a sell signal occurs

68
00:05:50,970 --> 00:05:55,830
If we analyze this chart, we can observe some
decent signals offered by the Chaikin Money

69
00:05:55,830 --> 00:05:57,310
Flow indicator.

70
00:05:57,310 --> 00:06:04,370
But being a volume indicator, by itself, the
CMF is not so reliable and it will offer many

71
00:06:04,370 --> 00:06:05,600
false signals.

72
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:10,220
It’s better to confirm the trend with another
indicator.

73
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:16,470
In this case, I like to use my old reliable
200-period moving average in order to determine

74
00:06:16,470 --> 00:06:18,780
the prevailing trend.

75
00:06:18,780 --> 00:06:24,370
• When the price trades above the 200-period
exponential moving average, we consider taking

76
00:06:24,370 --> 00:06:26,850
only long entries.

77
00:06:26,850 --> 00:06:31,410
• When the price trades below the 200-period
exponential moving average we consider taking

78
00:06:31,410 --> 00:06:33,150
only short entries.

79
00:06:33,150 --> 00:06:37,030
Now, entering the market is much simpler.

80
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:43,270
We wait for the Chaikin Money Flow indicator
to cross above the 0-level, above 200-EMA

81
00:06:43,270 --> 00:06:49,900
for a long entry and we wait Chaikin Money
Flow indicator to cross below the 0-level,

82
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:54,530
below 200-EMA for a short entry.

83
00:06:54,530 --> 00:06:56,610
And here an even better entry.

84
00:06:56,610 --> 00:07:04,070
A smarter way to trade the Chaikin Money Flow
would be to plot the 0.05 and -0.05 levels.

85
00:07:04,070 --> 00:07:09,890
In this way, you filter the choppiness around
the 0 level.

86
00:07:09,890 --> 00:07:20,430
• Take short entries below -0.05 level
• Take long positions above the 0.05 level

87
00:07:20,430 --> 00:07:43,810
Here are a few examples of valid CMF trades.

88
00:07:43,810 --> 00:07:48,350
Another strategy involves applying a moving
average on the indicator.

89
00:07:48,350 --> 00:07:52,520
By adding a moving average on the Chaikin
Money Flow’s chart window, you can take

90
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:57,500
crossover signals,
Now, when you want to trade a crossover between

91
00:07:57,500 --> 00:08:01,770
the Chaikin Money Flow oscillator and a moving
average, you should be aware of an important

92
00:08:01,770 --> 00:08:02,770
thing.

93
00:08:02,770 --> 00:08:07,000
A crossover will catch good movements when
markets are trending.

94
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:11,570
When markets are trading in a range, this
system is subject to false signals, which

95
00:08:11,570 --> 00:08:13,110
will lead to losing trades.

96
00:08:13,110 --> 00:08:19,470
A longer-term moving average added on Chaikin
Money Flow will work better than short-term

97
00:08:19,470 --> 00:08:20,490
moving average.

98
00:08:20,490 --> 00:08:24,970
A longer-term moving average will produce
fewer signals.

99
00:08:24,970 --> 00:08:27,370
Also, this is not enough.

100
00:08:27,370 --> 00:08:31,500
This approach will generate many false signals
if you don’t confirm the trend with other

101
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:32,840
indicators.

102
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:36,759
You cannot take a crossover signal without
knowing the market trend.

103
00:08:36,759 --> 00:08:43,189
That’s why I prefer to determine the prevailing
trend in the market with Ichimoku indicator.

104
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:47,870
For this setup, I plot only the Kumo cloud.

105
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:53,790
So we plotted the Kumo cloud and we added
a 200-period moving average on the Chaikin

106
00:08:53,790 --> 00:08:57,720
Money Flow indicator with a 21-period input.

107
00:08:57,720 --> 00:09:02,810
And the setup is simple:
• Buy only signals above the Kumo cloud,

108
00:09:02,810 --> 00:09:06,470
when the Chaikin Money Flow crosses above
the 200-period moving average

109
00:09:06,470 --> 00:09:15,450
• Sell only signals below the Kumo cloud,
when the Chaikin Money Flow crosses below

110
00:09:15,450 --> 00:09:16,769
200-period moving average

111
00:09:16,769 --> 00:09:25,209
Also, very important…We don’t take entries
when the price is inside the Kumo cloud.

112
00:09:25,209 --> 00:09:30,779
If a crossover between Chaikin Money Flow
and the 200 EMA occurs when the market price

113
00:09:30,779 --> 00:09:34,459
is inside the Kumo cloud, we ignore the setup.

114
00:09:34,459 --> 00:09:39,920
We could enter a trade once the price closes
above or below the cloud, in the direction

115
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:41,610
indicated by the crossover.

116
00:09:41,610 --> 00:09:45,730
But never when the price is inside.

117
00:09:45,730 --> 00:10:11,339
Here are some examples of valid trades, with
the Kumo cloud as trend filter.

118
00:10:11,339 --> 00:10:16,420
Chaikin Money Flow is a very useful indicator
for confirming the direction of the main trend.

119
00:10:16,420 --> 00:10:21,379
It works well during trending market conditions
and is very good at confirming the strength

120
00:10:21,379 --> 00:10:23,110
of the main trend.

121
00:10:23,110 --> 00:10:28,509
In what concerns its limitations, in a choppy
market, many false signals are generated around

122
00:10:28,509 --> 00:10:31,649
the zero level, so be aware of this.

123
00:10:31,649 --> 00:10:38,579
Also, CMF value is not accurate when big gaps
occur on the market so when you spot larger

124
00:10:38,579 --> 00:10:42,779
gaps, maybe you should re-analyze the setup.

125
00:10:42,779 --> 00:10:48,730
I also found the Chaikin Money Flow quite
unreliable on smaller time frames like M1

126
00:10:48,730 --> 00:10:55,670
or M5, so I would pay extra attention when
using it for scalping.

127
